CREATE TABLE Employer
(
	Employer_ID INTEGER,
	FullName TEXT,
	JoiningDate DATE,
	CurrentPosition TEXT,
	Department TEXT,
	AssignedProject TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE Services(
	Software_ID INTEGER,
	Name TEXT,
	Category TEXT,
	Size INTEGER,
	NumberOfInstallment INTEGER
)

CREATE TABLE Software_Requests
(
	Employer_ID INTEGER,
	Software_ID INTEGER,
	Request_Start_Date DATE,
	Request_Close_Date DATE,
	Status TEXT
)

I should use a trigger that would increment NumberOfInstallmet of the proper software by one after a request was inserted.

I would create a stored procedure to make a request invalid. It would automatically decrease the number of installments of that software when it is called. The IT team should use this stored procedure whenever they want to flag a request invalid.


